OPEN AI FINE TUNING
openai api files.create -p fine-tune -f ac_testcases.jsonl
openai api files.create -f ac_testcases.jsonl -p fine-tune
 - get file id
openai api fine_tuning.jobs.create -t file-abc123xyz456 -m gpt-3.5-turbo
openai api fine_tuning.jobs.list

ft:gpt-3.5-turbo:your-org:custom:testcase-gen





✅ What You Can Do on Azure Instead
1. Use Prompt Engineering
Craft structured prompts like:

“Generate test cases from this acceptance criteria: AC - User should receive a password reset email.”

2. Build a RAG System (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)
Instead of fine-tuning:

Store AC ↔ test case pairs in a vector database (e.g., Azure Cognitive Search or Pinecone)

Embed them using text-embedding-ada-002

Use similarity search + GPT to generate or retrieve test cases

3. Use Azure Machine Learning (Custom Models)
If you truly need fine-tuning:

Train your own small language model (like BERT or T5) using Azure ML or Hugging Face Transformers

Deploy it via Azure ML endpoints



